en.name: Surgeon Rifles 1581 XL action .338 LM bolt-action sniper rifle
en.description: Manufactured by Surgeon Rifles, the Surgeon 1581 Long Action is machined from a solid piece of billet steel and comes with equipped with an integral 20 MOA rail and recoil lug. Based off of the Remington 700 footprint, the Surgeon 1581 works with Remington 700 triggers and fits in most stocks and chassis inlet for the Remington 700.

en.name: Badger Ordnance IMUNS for AICS 2.0 chassis
en.description: The Badger Ordnance IMUNS installs into any Accuracy International Chassis 2.0 (except AS 50s), replaces the current bipod mounting block and allows the use of clip on night vision devices such as the A/N PVS-22, A/N PVS-24, A/N PVS-27 or other devices like thermal imagers or fusion devices.

en.name: Badger Ordnance IMUNS side rail
en.description: The Badger Ordnance IMUNS installs into any Accuracy International Chassis 2.0 (except AS 50s), replaces the current bipod mounting block and allows the use of clip on night vision devices such as the A/N PVS-22, A/N PVS-24, A/N PVS-27 or other devices like thermal imagers or fusion devices.

en.name: MDT XTN to buffer tube adapter
en.description: The MDT XTN (ESS + ACC) AR Adapter converts the proprietary XTN buttstock interface to a standard AR-style carbine buffer tube interface.

en.name: PGW Defense C14 Timberwolf .338 LM sound suppressor
en.description: The Prarie Gun Works sound suppressor designed to be used as a part of the C14 Medium Range Sniper Weapon System (MRSWS) boasts a very quiet report, using the same style sleeving suppressor as the AEM5 suppressor used by the MK12 SPR. While keeping the noise down, it also has a very limited POI shift, making it perfect for the Canadian army that uses it to this day.

en.name: PGW Defense C14 .338 LM muzzle brake
en.description: The Prarie Gun Works muzzle brake designed to be used as a part of the C14 Medium Range Sniper Weapon System (MRSWS), using a clamp on style system known for how secure it is on a precision rifle barrel.

en.name: AR-15 MDT Elite pistol grip
en.description: The MDT pistol grip has been designed to provide superior ergonomics with insight from expert shooters experience and preferences. Compatible with MDT Chassis Systems as well as a standard AR-15 interface.

en.name: McMillan A5 stock for Remington 700 long action (BLK)
en.description: The A-5 stock combines all the most requested features of the entire A-series into one professional tactical rifle stock. Compared to our other A-series stocks, the A-5 uses a beavertail forearm that is wider and flatter. The action and barrel sit lower for enhanced stability. The A-5 uses a trim pistol grip.

en.name: McMillan A5 stock for Remington 700 long action (FDE)
en.description: The A-5 stock combines all the most requested features of the entire A-series into one professional tactical rifle stock. Compared to our other A-series stocks, the A-5 uses a beavertail forearm that is wider and flatter. The action and barrel sit lower for enhanced stability. The A-5 uses a trim pistol grip.

en.name: McMillan A5 stock for Remington 700 long action (ODG)
en.description: The A-5 stock combines all the most requested features of the entire A-series into one professional tactical rifle stock. Compared to our other A-series stocks, the A-5 uses a beavertail forearm that is wider and flatter. The action and barrel sit lower for enhanced stability. The A-5 uses a trim pistol grip.

en.name: Accuracy International AT AICS chassis for Remington 700 long action
en.description: The rugged platform of the AICS combines the leading characteristics of steel and polymer. Featuring a full-length, aluminum, self-aligning, self-bedding vee block this system more than supersedes traditional bedding practices. This model has had the thumbhole upgrade applied.

en.name: MDT ESS chassis for Remington 700 long action
en.description: The MDT ESS Chassis System introduced a lot of features that have since driven design decisions on MDT chassis moving forward, such as the M-LOK forend, ambidextrous magazine latch, and the XTN buttstock interface that allows room for your hand to sit naturally.

en.name: MDT Carbine buffer tube
en.description: A standard buffer tube produced by MDT for use in their ESS chassis with an adapter, however it works fine in an AR-15 as well.

en.name: MDT SRS-X stock
en.description: Toolless adjustment of the MDT Skeleton Rifle Stock elevates the comfort and performance of the shooter. Horizontal, vertical and cant adjustment to the cheek riser and buttpad ensures a perfect fit for your shooting position.
